org.anyframe.idgen.impl.strategy
Class MixPrefixStrategy

java.lang.Object
  org.anyframe.idgen.impl.strategy.MixPrefixStrategy
All Implemented Interfaces:
IdGenStrategy
Deprecated. This class is replaced to MixStrategy.class. Use MixStrategy class. 

public class MixPrefixStrategy
extends Object
implements IdGenStrategy

MixPrefix is a kind of id generation strategy. MixPrefix assembles prefix, original string, paddingChar into new id. For example,
prefix is a 'TEST-'
paddingChar is a '0'
original string is a '12'
and maxCiphers is a 5
in result, new id is a 'TEST-00012'. * The Configuration to use a MixPrefixStrategy looks like the following: 

  <property name="prefix" value="TEST-"/>     
  <property name="maxCiphers" value="5"/>
  <property name="paddingChar" value="0"/>

Author:
SoYon Lim
